<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Tea — Brew-Inspired Terms That Score Big"
  description="Tea and brewing words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHAMOMILE (18pts), MATCHA (13pts), OOLONG (7pts). Tea vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble tea words, chamomile scrabble points, matcha scrabble, oolong scrabble, tea terms scrabble, brewing words scrabble, herbal vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Tea — Brew-Inspired Terms That Score Big","description":"Tea and brewing words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHAMOMILE (18pts), MATCHA (13pts), OOLONG (7pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-tea"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CHAMOMILE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CHAMOMILE scores 18 points (C=3, H=4, A=1, M=3, O=1, M=3, I=1, L=1, E=1) as a 9-letter word. It refers to the herbal plant used for soothing tea. Valid in SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play MATCHA in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. MATCHA scores 13 points (M=3, A=1, T=1, C=3, H=4, A=1). It's a 6-letter word referring to powdered green tea. The H=4 and double 3-point tiles give it good value."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is OOLONG valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! OOLONG scores 7 points (O=1, O=1, L=1, O=1, N=1, G=2) as a 6-letter word. It's a type of Chinese tea. While low-scoring, it's excellent for dumping multiple O tiles from your rack."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Tea — Brew-Inspired Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The world of tea offers a surprisingly rich vocabulary for Scrabble players. From herbal infusions to ceremonial preparations, tea terminology contains valuable H tiles, M tiles, and C tiles that can steep your score in points.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHAMOMILE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MATCHA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">OOLONG</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BREWING</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Tea Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CHAMOMILE — 18 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, H=4, A=1, M=3, O=1, M=3, I=1, L=1, E=1 · 9 letters</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The soothing herbal plant used in bedtime teas. CHAMOMILE is a 9-letter powerhouse scoring 18 base points. The H=4, double M=3, and C=3 combine for a strong play that also earns 50 bonus points as a bingo-plus word.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍵 MATCHA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · M=3, A=1, T=1, C=3, H=4, A=1 · Green tea powder</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫖 OOLONG</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · O=1, O=1, L=1, O=1, N=1, G=2 · Chinese tea</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">☕ BREWING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · B=3, R=1, E=1, W=4, I=1, N=1, G=2 · 7-letter bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌿 HERBAL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · H=4, E=1, R=1, B=3, A=1, L=1 · Tea type</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tea Ceremony Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>Words from tea culture provide solid mid-scoring options that use common tiles effectively:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STEEP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">INFUSE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KETTLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TISANE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAFFEINE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Tea Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OOLONG dumps triple O:</span> Stuck with three O tiles? OOLONG uses them all while scoring 7 points. It cleans your rack for better draws next turn.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MATCHA pairs M, C, and H:</span> These three tiles (M=3, C=3, H=4) total 10 points alone. MATCHA uses them efficiently in 6 tiles for 13 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BREWING is a bingo builder:</span> At 7 letters (B=3, R=1, E=1, W=4, I=1, N=1, G=2), BREWING earns 9 base + 50 bonus = 59 points. The W=4 and B=3 make it better than most common bingos.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Tea words are <span class="text-white font-medium">H-tile and M-tile specialists</span>. CHAMOMILE, MATCHA, HERBAL, and CHAI all leverage H=4 and M=3. When you draw H and M together, think tea — the vocabulary pairs them naturally with common vowels for reliable scores.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-coffee/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Coffee</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-herbs/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Herbs</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-cooking/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Cooking</span></a>
        </div>
